<item>
            <title>[LU-4238] Request for client parameter to limit caching of Lustre files to no larger than a certain size</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4238</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Use case:  Clients performing buffered IO in a mixed (small and large files) workload.  Goal is to increase performance by keeping the small files in cache.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Justification:  Ability to avoid caching of large files should keep small files in cache, thereby increasing performance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Implementation:  Thinking that a parameter, like the obdfilter.*.readcache_max_filesize parameter on an OSS, could be used.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="21951">LU-4238</key>
            <summary>Request for client parameter to limit caching of Lustre files to no larger than a certain size</summary>
