                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="71193" author="rread" created="Sat, 9 Nov 2013 01:17:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The caching on the client side is done by the Linux pageacache and is not done directly by Lustre.  However, Lustre might be able to place pages on the end (or the beginning) of the LRU queue so they would be reclaimed immediately. Applications can also do this themselves by using the fadvise() syscall when they open a file.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
